rivacy Policy for Into the Wild Seas

Effective Date: July 2026

Welcome to Into the Wild Seas. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your information. This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected when you use our game and how it is used.

Information We Collect

Into the Wild Seas does not require you to create an account.

Depending on the features you use, third-party services may collect limited information necessary to provide game functionality, including:

Device identifiers required by Google Play Services.
Game progress and achievements if you choose to sign in with Google Play Games.
Basic technical information needed to operate the game.

We do not collect personal information such as:

Name
Email address
Phone number
Home address
Payment information
Google Play Games

Signing in with Google Play Games is completely optional.

If you choose to sign in, Google may process your information according to its own Privacy Policy.

How We Use Information

Information is used only to:

Save your game progress (when using Google Play Games)
Enable online game features
Improve game performance and compatibility
Diagnose technical issues
Third-Party Services

The game may use:

Google Play Games Services
Google Play Services

These services operate under Google's own privacy policies.

Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.

Any information processed by Google services is handled according to Google's own policies.

Children's Privacy

Into the Wild Seas is not intended to collect personal information from children.

Data Security

We take reasonable steps to help protect information processed through the game.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.

